modules.description: This module implements the Kuznechik block cipher algorithm, providing functions to create a cipher instance from a key and to encrypt or decrypt 128-bit blocks. It operates on 128-bit data blocks represented as arrays of integers, using a precomputed key schedule stored in the cipher instance. Typical use cases include secure data encryption and decryption in cryptographic applications requiring the GOST R 34.12-2015 standard.

This module implements the Kuznechik block cipher algorithm, enabling encryption and decryption of 128-bit data blocks using a key schedule derived from a given key. It provides functions to initialize a cipher instance with a key and perform encryption or decryption on 128-bit blocks represented as integer arrays. For example, it can be used to securely encrypt sensitive data according to the GOST R 34.12-2015 standard or decrypt previously encrypted blocks in a cryptographic application.
